<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8106&amp;p=83629#p83629</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8106&amp;p=83629#p83629"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Other uses for the SPC700 besides sound.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8106&amp;p=83629#p83629"><![CDATA[
Like what? It can only communicate with the SCPU via a slow communication method. Even if you used the SPC to communicate with the SCPU to feed it some sort of calculations it would be faster to do it on the SCPU. The only thing I could think of you might consider is using the SPC to hide some sort of copy protection code where you process encrypted data in the SPC to try to hide it from less involved hackers or something.<br /><br />The SPC really is just meant for playing music and sound effects. It's clocked too slow and has too slow of communication with the SCPU to be useful for anything else.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Thu Sep 08, 2011 12:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
